@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Cookie Policy";
}
<div class="container">
    <h1 class="mt-5 mb-3">@ViewData["Title"]</h1>
</div>

<div class="container my-5">
    <p><em>Last updated: [Date]</em></p>

    <h2 class="mt-5">1. What Are Cookies?</h2>
    <p>
        Cookies are small text files placed on your device when you visit a website. They help the website remember your actions and preferences over time, such as login status, language selection, and other settings.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-5">2. How We Use Cookies</h2>
    <p>
        SubtitleTranslator uses cookies to:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Authenticate and keep you logged in</li>
        <li>Remember your language and display preferences</li>
        <li>Track anonymous usage statistics to improve performance</li>
        <li>Enable secure transactions and protect against fraud</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="mt-5">3. Types of Cookies We Use</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Strictly Necessary Cookies:</strong> Required for the app to function properly (e.g., login session).</li>
        <li><strong>Functional Cookies:</strong> Remember user preferences like selected language or layout.</li>
        <li><strong>Analytics Cookies:</strong> Help us understand how users interact with the site (e.g., Google Analytics).</li>
        <li><strong>Third-Party Cookies:</strong> Used by services like Stripe or SendGrid to support functionality or fraud prevention.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="mt-5">4. Managing Cookies</h2>
    <p>
        You can control and manage cookies in your browser settings. Most browsers allow you to:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>View and delete existing cookies</li>
        <li>Block third-party cookies</li>
        <li>Disable all cookies completely (may break functionality)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        For more detailed instructions, visit:
        <a href="https://www.aboutcookies.org/" target="_blank">aboutcookies.org</a>
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-5">5. Consent to Use Cookies</h2>
    <p>
        By using the SubtitleTranslator app, you consent to our use of cookies as described in this policy.
        When required by law, we will display a cookie banner and ask for your explicit consent before storing cookies.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-5">6. Changes to This Cookie Policy</h2>
    <p>
        We may update this Cookie Policy periodically. We will inform users of significant changes via email or in-app messages.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-5">7. Contact Us</h2>
    <p>
        If you have questions about our cookie practices, please contact us:<br>
        📧 <a href="mailto:support@email.com">support@email.com</a><br>
        📍 [Company Address]
    </p>
</div>


